---
title: Chesapeake Cheddar Burgers with Potato Wedges & Old Bay® Aioli
description: In this extra-savory spin on burger night, spicy Old Bay seasoning and savory Worcestershire sauce add oomph to beef patties. Griddle to perfection, add cheddar slices, then tuck them into golden toasted brioche buns spread with what we call “Old Bay-oli”—that’s mayo, mustard, garlic, and Old Bay! Serve with seasoned potato wedges on the side.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66156959d0360c342f04b50c-5c47e968.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66156959d0360c342f04b50c.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 1130 kcal
  fat: 75 g
  saturated fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1230 mg
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chesapeake-cheddar-burgers-66156959d0360c342f04b50c
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, thinly slice @Tomato{1} into rounds.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon},
1 tsp water, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, and @OLD BAY® Seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}.
Set aside until ready to use in Step 4.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, 1⁄2 tsp OLD BAY® Seasoning,
and 1⁄4 tsp @Worcestershire Sauce{1%tablespoon}.

> Save any remaining OLD BAY® Seasoning and Worcestershire sauce for another use!

Form beef mixture into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a
burger bun. Season lightly with pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add patties and cook until
browned and cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top each patty with @Cheddar Cheese{2%slice};
cover pan until cheese melts.

While patties cook, halve and toast @Brioche Buns{2} until golden.

Spread a thin layer of OLD BAY® aioli on cut sides of bottom buns. Top with patties,
tomato slices, and top buns.

Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve with remaining OLD BAY®
aioli on the side for dipping.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.